A pan-Nigeria political support group, South-West Agenda for Tinubu (SWAGA 6), comprising of members from the six geopolitical zones of the country, has celebrated its convener and matron, Alhaja Kafilat Ogbara, on the auspicious occasion of her birthday anniversary on Monday. In a statement released by the group and signed by its national publicity secretary, Babajide Akinbohun, SWAGA 6 described the convener of SWAGA, Mrs. Ogbara, as a woman of virtue with impeccable character, who has remained dedicated to the advancement of women and development of youth in the country. “Today, we celebrate our mother, matron, mentor, philanthropist and friend, as she attains a new age. You have done so much for humanity and your efforts will not go unrewarded. We appreciate you for the lives that you have touched, tears that you have wiped away from many families and hopes that you have given to the downtrodden and underprivileged in our society. “We salute your courage, doggedness and commitment to nation building through your activities within the progressives fold. You have shown excellence, dedication and an uncommon bravery in all the assignments that you have previously undertaken. Your politics of conviction has spurred us to further believe in your leadership qualities. As a partner in progress, we celebrate you today for all your giant strides towards humanity and we look forward to many more accomplishments in the coming years. It is our fervent prayers that Almighty Allah will grant you long life, more wisdom and knowledge in all your endeavors,” Akinbohun stated.